name: iShares S&P/TSX Energy Transition Materials Index ETF
longDescription: The ETF currently seeks to replicate the performance of the S&P/TSX Energy Transition Materials Index (the Index). The Index measures the performance of North American listed securities engaged in the mining, exploration, or manufacturing of products using alumina, aluminum, bauxite, cobalt, copper, lithium, manganese, molybdenum, nickel, palladium, platinum, rare earth metals, silver, uranium, and zinc (as determined by the index provider). Under normal market conditions, XETM will primarily invest in Canadian and international equity securities and/or securities of one or more ETFs managed by BlackRock or an affiliate. The ETF seeks to provide longterm capital growth.
